  <titles>
    <title as="introduced" type="short">Tip Tax Fairness Act of 2003</title>
    <title as="introduced" type="official">To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to provide that an employer shall be liable for Social Security taxes on unreported tips paid to an employee only after the Internal Revenue Service establishes the amount of tips received by that employee.</title>
